The student performs a full practice observing, analyzing, and providing physics lessons of elementary school stage III (grades 7 to 9). The student teacher gives independently 10 physics lessons within 12 weeks.  At the end of school practice student will compile and present the portfolio according to the instructions of pedagogical practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1. To integrate theoretical knowledge into practice. 2. To get to know teaching and learning process. 3. To acquire the teaching management skills. 4. To develope subject-based and professional competences. 5. To develpe an analysing skill of pedagogical situations, problems and relationships.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of school practice the learner: 1. Is able to plan, carry out, analyse and evaluate his/her teaching and learning activities. 2. Is able to analyse himself/herself as the teacher in different roles.
